LiquidationExplanationStmt.ExplanationTxt: ON DECEMBER 29, 2020, THE A. CHUDNOW AND SONS HISTORICAL MUSEUM, INC.("CMY") ENTERED INTO AN AGREEMENT TO TRANSFER THE MAJORITY OF ITS COLLECTION OF ARTWORKS, COLLECTIBLES, DISPLAY MATERIALS AND RELATED ITEMS TO THE CEDARBURG LANDMARK PRESERVATION SOCIETY, INC. ("CHM"). IN ADDITION, CMY AGREED TO PROVIDE 50% OF THE SALES PROCEEDS FROM THE SALE OF CMY'S BUILDINGS TO CHM FOR PURPOSES OF SUPPORTING AND ENDOWING THE CMY COLLECTION AT CHM. BASED ON THE EVENTS OF COVID AND THE INCREASING OPERATING EXPENSES OF STAYING INDEPENDENT, CMY DETERMINED IT WAS IN THE BEST INTERESTS OF CONTINUING ITS EDUCATIONAL AND NOT FOR PROFIT ACTIVITIES IN CONJUNCTION WITH CHM TO LOWER OVERHEAD AND PROVIDE A BETTER OVERALL EXPERIENCE FOR THE USERS OF ITS COLLECTION. CMY LIQUIDATED REMAINING ITEMS OF INVENTORY AND THE COLLECTION DURING THIS YEAR, AND REMAINING ASSETS WERE DISTRIBUTED TO OTHER 501(C)(3) NOT FOR PROFIT ENTITIES AS DETAILED IN PART XIV.
